'''Dunya University of Afghanistan''' is a private university established in 2009 in [[Kabul]], [[Afghanistan]] in partnership with the [[Swiss UMEF University]].<ref>{{cite web|title=DUA History|url=http://www.dunya.edu.af/history-dua/|publisher=Dunya University of Afghanistan|accessdate=20 February 2017}}</ref> UMEF is not accredited by the Swiss higher education authorities.<ref>{{cite web|title=Recognised or Accredited Swiss Higher Education Institutions|url=https://www.swissuniversities.ch/en/higher-education-area/recognised-swiss-higher-education-institutions/|publisher=swissuniversities|accessdate=20 February 2017}}</ref>
Dunya University is recognized by the Ministry of Higher Education of Afghanistan,<ref>{{cite web|title=Universities|url=http://www.mohe.gov.af/p_university/en|website=mohe.gov.af|language=en|accessdate=2 March 2017}}</ref> and its academic business units were accredited by the [[International Assembly for Collegiate Business Education]] as of December 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=News Release - Recent Accreditations|url=http://iacbe.org/news-releases-recent-accreditations-1216.asp|website=IACBE.org|accessdate=2 March 2017}}</ref>
DUA is a member of the [[Accreditation Council for Business Schools and Programs]] (ACBSP),<ref>{{cite web|title=Educational Members - Accreditation Council for Business Schools and Programs|url=http://www.acbsp.org/page/membership_list|website=acbsp.org|language=en|accessdate=2 March 2017}}</ref> and the [[Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business]].<ref name="aacsb">{{cite web|title=DataDirect - General - Dunya University of Afghanistan|url=https://datadirect.aacsb.edu/public/profiles/profile.cfm?interstitialComplete=1&runReport=1&unitid=106448&userType=All|website=datadirect.aacsb.edu|publisher=AACSB|accessdate=2 March 2017}}</ref> Membership in these organization does not imply accreditation, although ACBSP is recognized as an accrediting body by the [[Council for Higher Education Accreditation]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Directories - Programmatic - 2016-2017|url=http://www.chea.org/4DCGI/cms/review.html?Action=CMS_Document&DocID=200&MenuKey=main/|website=chea.org|accessdate=2 March 2017}}</ref> The AACSB report on DUA states that DUA is not accredited.<ref name="aacsb"/>
