==History== Setanta College was founded by [[Liam Hennessy (coach)|Dr. Liam Hennessy]] BA, MSc, PhD,FRAMI,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.setantacollege.com/staff/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-03-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120215104539/http://www.setantacollege.com/staff/ |archivedate=15 February 2012 |df= }}</ref> a former international [[Pole Vault]] competitor and record holder.<ref>http://archives.tcm.ie/irishexaminer/2000/01/20/current/spage_7.htm{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Dr. Hennessy, an [[Exercise Physiologist]] and [[strength and conditioning coach]] who is also published in scientific journals<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1136/bjsm.27.4.243 |pmid=8130961 |pmc=1332012 |title=Flexibility and posture assessment in relation to hamstring injury |journal=British Journal of Sports Medicine |volume=27 |issue=4 |pages=243–6 |year=1993 |last1=Hennessey |first1=L. |last2=Watson |first2=A. W. }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1080/14763140601058540 |pmid=17542178 |title=Identifying the optimal resistive load for complex training in male rugby players |journal=Sports Biomechanics |volume=6 |issue=1 |pages=59–70 |year=2007 |last1=Comyns |first1=Thomas M. |last2=Harrison |first2=Andrew J. |last3=Hennessy |first3=Liam |last4=Jensen |first4=Randall L. |hdl=10344/5639 }}</ref> and has worked with some top athletes and sports teams, including leading European soccer club teams in Italy,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tribune.maithu.com/archive/article/2000/sep/17/doctors-orders-less-work-more-rest/|title=Sign in|website=GitLab}}{{dead link|date=May 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> and Germany,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sixmilebridgegaa.com/news/showfullnewsstory.asp?id%3D312%26category%3Dlatestnews |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-03-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131112102325/http://www.sixmilebridgegaa.com/news/showfullnewsstory.